issue.body:
I was getting an issue in a gulp build environment where my svg icon builder mixing was incorrectly outputting the css styles

```
.image {
    background-image: url('../image.png');
    .svg & {
        background-image: data-uri('image.svg');
    }
}
```

This should output something like

```
 .image{
    background-image: url('../image.png');
  }
  .svg .image {
    background-image: url(data:image/svg+xml;base64,);
  }
```

But I'm getting:

```
 .image{
    background-image: url('../image.png');
  }
  .svg .image {
    background-image: url("data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg%22%20x%3D%220px%22%20y%3D%220px%22%20width%3D%222px%22%20height%3D%222px%22%20viewBox%3D%220%200%202%202%22%3E%3Crect%20width%3D%222%22%20height%3D%221%22%20%20fill%3D%22%23000000%22%20%2F%3E%3Crect%20y%3D%221%22%20fill%3D%22%233C3C3C%22%20width%3D%222%22%20height%3D%221%22%2F%3E%3C%2Fsvg%3E");
  }
```

Initially, I downgraded gulp-less to gulp-less@1.3.6 and this fixed the issue, I then incrementally upgraded through the gulp-less versions until the css output looked wrong again, and I found that immediately upgrading to gulp-less@1.3.7 caused the issue to appear.

So that fixed the gulp-less issue, but then I checked my old build tool, I used Koala and had it set to use the local/system less compiler and checking the installed version that was less@2.4.0 and I was getting the same data-uri compile issue.

Again I downgraded my local less back to less@1.7.5 and the outputted css complied as expected.
I've then incrementally upgraded thorough the versions of less and tested the compile using koala and found that version less@2.0.0 caused the issue.

Is the change in output an intended feature and I've missed a setting, or a bug?

Thanks
